parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult or impossible to turn, leading to a loss of vehicle control and increasing the risk of accidents.

the steering wheel jerks or vibrates
and the vehicle may become stuck in a turn.
